<%#
  First-run / zero-project empty state (projects.md §6, §13-S6). Under Design B a
  monitor and an API key both live inside a project, so before anything else the
  user creates their first project. Shown on the dashboard (no projects yet) and
  on an empty projects index (e.g. after deleting the last project). The gem copy
  is honest: a project's API key is required before the gem registers anything —
  not the old "zero setup, your jobs register themselves" pitch.
%>
<div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-surface p-10 shadow-sm text-center max-w-xl mx-auto"
     data-testid="first-project-empty-state">
  <div class="flex justify-center mb-4"><%= render "shared/logo", size: 44 %></div>
  <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">Create your first project</h2>
  <p class="mt-1 text-[13px] text-muted">
    A project groups the monitors for one app. Create one, then add monitors or
    connect the gem with the project's API key.
  </p>

  <%# Inline create (§3): a brand-new user makes their first project without an
      extra page load. Validation errors still fall back to projects#new. %>
  <%= form_with model: current_user.projects.new, url: projects_path,
        class: "mt-5 flex items-center justify-center gap-2",
        data: { testid: "create-first-project" } do |form| %>
    <%= form.label :name, "Project name", class: "sr-only" %>
    <%= form.text_field :name, required: true, placeholder: "Project name",
          class: "h-9 w-56 px-3 rounded-lg border border-border text-[13px] focus:outline-brand" %>
    <%= form.submit "Create project",
          class: "h-9 px-4 rounded-lg bg-brand text-white text-[13px] font-semibold hover:bg-brand-hover cursor-pointer" %>
  <% end %>

  <div class="mt-8 text-left">
    <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-gem mb-2">Connect the gem</p>
    <%= render "shared/recurring_yml_snippet" %>
    <p class="mt-2 text-[12px] text-muted">
      Create a project, then copy its API key into your app — the gem uses that
      key to register the project's jobs. A key is required before the gem does
      anything. <%= link_to "Read the gem guide →", "#", class: "text-brand font-medium" %>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
